This paper deals with sentiment analysis of social media data, which falls under the category of natural language processing (NLP). Therefore, cs.CL (Computation and Language) is the most likely sub-category. The paper also discusses the use of rule-based and supervised models, which are common techniques in machine learning and artificial intelligence (cs.AI). The development of hybrid systems also involves techniques from machine learning and data analysis, which could fall under cs.LG (Machine Learning) and cs.SI (Social and Information Networks). Finally, the paper discusses the use of metrics and evaluation methods, which could fall under cs.IR (Information Retrieval).
